  "market_context": "BTC sold off from highs near 112,000 toward the 98,000–100,000 area. On the 4-hour, a clear bullish fair value gap was left below as price expanded down, with a swing low forming near 98,200 before recovering back toward 103,000.",
  "key_observation": "Once the 4H low formed and the 4H fair value gap was identified as the higher timeframe target, the analyst dropped to the 15-minute fractal model to find a protected low with a sweep-and-closure, then continuations back into the 4H FVG.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Move from the daily context to the hourly to search for a tradeable model and a respected reaction area (T-spot).",
    "Step up to the 4-hour timeframe and identify a clear 4H fair value gap as the higher-timeframe draw on liquidity.",
    "Drop down to the 15-minute fractal model on BTC to find a sweep of the prior low and a closure through it (C2), confirming a protected low.",
    "Wait for consolidation after the protected low and look for a sweep of that consolidation to enter long for continuation higher.",
    "Cross-check with correlated asset ETH on the 15-minute, which shows a cleaner protected low with continuations toward the same higher-timeframe target.",
    "Plan entry with stop beneath the protected low, targeting a minimum 2R toward the 4H fair value gap fill."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price expanded higher into the 4H fair value gap area without the analyst; he noted the entry would have been valid for 2R, especially cleaner on the ETH correlated chart.",
  "lessons": "Higher-timeframe context dictates the target (4H FVG); the entry timeframe is flexible. As long as a protected swing is confirmed with sweep-and-closure, dropping to the 15-minute fractal model provides precise, low-risk entries toward HTF objectives.",
